n. In Proceedings of the AAAI Conference on Artificial Intelligence, volume 36, 11765–11773.\n23504"}, {"url": "https://research.google/blog/assessing-asr-performance-with-meaning-preservation", "title": "Assessing ASR performance with meaning preservation", "content": "MeaningPreservation1-TableFin\n\nWith this in mind, we set out to create a system that will automatically assess the ability of an ASR model to effectively convey the user’s intended message. In our paper “Large Language Models as a Proxy for Human Evaluation in Assessing the Comprehensibility of Disordered Speech Transcription” (ICASSP 2024), we introduce a novel approach using a large language model (LLM) to determine whether a transcript accurately captures the intended meaning compared to a reference text. Building upon this approach, here we also report how using Gemini allows us to both use a significantly smaller model without much loss in performance as well as gain multi-linguality for our meaning assessment task without the need for additional training.", "score": 0.55478466, "raw_content": "## Explore our many areas of focus\n\n![earth_AI_nav](https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-research2023-media/original_images/earth_AI_nav.svg)\n![health_AI_nav](https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-research2023-media/original_images/health_AI_nav.svg)\n![science_AI_nav](https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-research2023-media/original_images/science_AI_nav.svg)\n![sustainability_crisis_resilience_nav](https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-research2023-media/original_images/sustainability_crisis_resilience_nav.svg)\n![algorithms_theory_nav](https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-research2023-media/original_images/algorithms_theory_nav.svg)\n![information_retrieval_nav](https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-research2023-media/original_images/information_retrieval_nav.svg)\n![machine_intelligence_nav](https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-research2023-media/original_images/machine_intelligence_nav.svg)\n![machine_perc