20](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12220090#CR20)] suggest potential gaps in validation. While the overall low risk in flow and timing strengthens confidence in the results, variability in methodological rigor underscores the need for standardised evaluation for future studies to ensure consistent and reliable conclusions.\n\nTable 3Detailed risk of bias assessment for the various studies using QUADAS-2 toolStudyRisk of biasApplicability concernsPatient SelectionIndex TestReference StandardFlow and TimingPatient SelectionIndex TestReference StandardAlmario et al., 2015 [[13](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12220090#CR13)]LOWLOWLOWLOWLOWLOWLOWAlmario et al., 2015 [[14](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12220090#CR14)]LOWLOWLOWLOWLOWLOWLOWBiro et al., 2025 [[32](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12220090#CR32)]LOWLOWLOWLOWLOWLOWLOWBlackley et al., 2020 [[21](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12220090#CR21)]HIGHLOWLOWLOWHIGHLOWLOWBalloch et al., 2024 [[4](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12220090#CR4)]LOWLOWLOWLOWLOWLOWLOWBundy et al., 2024 [[23](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12220090#CR23)]LOWLOWUNCLEARUNCLEARLOWLOWUNCLEARCao et al., 2024 [[24](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12220090#CR24)]LOWLOWLOWLOWLOWLOWLOWDuggan et al., 2025 [[33](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12220090#CR33)]LOWLOWLOWLOWLOWLOWLOWGoss et al., 2019 [[20](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12220090#CR20)]LOWUNCLEARUNCLEARUNCLEARLOWLOWUNCLEARHarbele et al., 2024 [[25](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12220090#CR25)]LOWLOWLOWLOWLOWLOWLOWHappe et al., 2003 [[10](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12220090#CR10)]UNCLEARUNCLEARLOWHIGHLOWLOWLOWHodgson et al., 2017 [[16](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12220090#CR16)]HIGHHIGHLOWLOWHIGHHIGHLOWIslam et al., 2024 [[26](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12220090#CR26)]LOWLOWLOWLOWLOWLOWLOWIssenman et al., 2004 [[12](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/a